Comment (src/views/dashboard/SuggestionsView.vue:478):
**Bug: `matched evidence` is always 0, and group label chips are empty.**

`evidenceCount` is read from `suggestion.evidenceCount`, but the API suggestion payload (`dashboardSuggestionResponse`) never includes that field — it only carries `labelSet` / `labelSetHash` (see `internal/service/relational/suggestions/models.go` `DashboardSuggestion` and `loadSuggestionResponses`, which joins only `controls.title` and `filters.name`). So `suggestion.evidenceCount ?? 0` is always `0`.

The real per-label-set count already exists on the `labelSets` array this component fetches via `refreshLabelSets()` (`LabelSetInput{ hash, labels, evidenceCount, sampleTitles }`). The hashes match: both the suggestion `labelSetHash` and the label-set `hash` come from the same `CanonicalLabelSetHash`, and `NormalizeLabelSet` only lowercases keys (it does NOT strip `_`-prefixed labels). So join by hash.

Also fix the empty label chips: the API field is `labelSet` (a map), but this code reads `suggestion.labels`, which is always `undefined` — so `formatLabelSet(suggestion.labels ?? {})` yields `[]`. Source the labels from the matched label-set instead.

Suggested implementation:

```ts
const labelSetByHash = computed(
  () => new Map((labelSets.value ?? []).map((ls) => [ls.hash, ls])),
);

const pendingGroups = computed(() => {
  const groups = new Map<string, { hash: string; labels: string[]; evidenceCount: number; sampleTitles: string[]; suggestions: DashboardSuggestion[] }>();
  for (const suggestion of pendingSuggestions.value ?? []) {
    const matched = labelSetByHash.value.get(suggestion.labelSetHash);
    const group = groups.get(suggestion.labelSetHash) ?? {
      hash: suggestion.labelSetHash,
      labels: formatLabelSet(matched?.labels ?? suggestion.labelSet ?? {}),
      evidenceCount: matched?.evidenceCount ?? 0,
      sampleTitles: matched?.sampleTitles ?? [],
      suggestions: [],
    };
    group.suggestions.push(suggestion);
    groups.set(suggestion.labelSetHash, group);
  }
  return Array.from(groups.values());
});
```

Note `matched?.labels` is preserved with underscores because `refreshLabelSets()` already passes `camelcaseStopPaths: ['data.labels']`. The `suggestion.labelSet` fallback (for when a stale suggestion's hash is no longer in the current `labelSets`) requires the companion change on the fetch in `useDashboardSuggestions.ts` — see that thread.
