Comment (src/views/dashboard/SuggestionsView.vue:137):
**Feature (B): make the matched-evidence count a link to the actual evidence.**

Once the count is correct (see the `pendingGroups` thread), users should be able to click through to see the matching evidence streams. The suggestion's `labelSet` IS a label filter, and the evidence index already filters by a `key=value and …` query string via `route.query.filter` (see `src/views/evidence/IndexView.vue`); there is also a `POST /evidence/search` endpoint that accepts a `labelfilter.Filter`.

Turn this span into a router-link to the evidence index pre-filtered by the group's labels. `group.labels` is already the array of `key=value` tokens produced by `formatLabelSet`, so the filter string is just `group.labels.join(' and ')`. For the GD.Conf.C02 example this becomes `_agent=… and _plugin=… and organization=compliance-framework and …`, which resolves to exactly the matching evidence stream(s).

Suggested change:

```vue
<router-link
  :to="{ name: 'evidence:index', query: { filter: group.labels.join(' and ') } }"
  class="text-sm text-zinc-500 hover:underline"
>
  {{ group.evidenceCount }} matched evidence
</router-link>
```

(Confirm the evidence route name — it is `evidence:index` in `src/router/index.ts`.) Optionally, render `group.sampleTitles` (up to 3, now available on the group) as a tooltip/preview so users get a glimpse without navigating away.
