Comment (src/composables/useDashboardSuggestions.ts:73):
**Companion change for the `labelSet` fallback: preserve underscore-prefixed label keys on the suggestion fetch.**

The pending/history suggestion fetches do not pass `camelcaseStopPaths`, so the global axios response interceptor deep-camelCases the `labelSet` map keys and strips the leading `_` (e.g. `_agent` → `agent`). That breaks any code that reads `suggestion.labelSet` directly — including the `suggestion.labelSet` fallback proposed in the `pendingGroups` thread (used when a stale suggestion's hash is no longer present in the current `labelSets`).

Add the stop path here, mirroring `refreshLabelSets()`:

```ts
return fetchPendingSuggestions(
  buildDashboardSuggestionsEndpoint(sspId.value, 'pending'),
  { camelcaseStopPaths: ['data.labelSet'] },
);
```

Apply the same `{ camelcaseStopPaths: ['data.labelSet'] }` option to the history fetch in `refreshHistorySuggestions` (the `fetchHistoryRequest(buildDashboardSuggestionsEndpoint(sspId.value, status))` call below). If you decide the count/labels join against `labelSets` is sufficient and drop the `suggestion.labelSet` fallback entirely, this change is not needed — but then a suggestion whose evidence has since changed will render 0 with no labels, so the fallback is recommended.
